commit.message:
free-examples: Fix some -Wx-partial warnings

These were uncovered by GHC 9.8, where -Wx-partial is included in -Wall.

Add back Functor/Applicative constraints to MonadTrans instances for FreeT

I had mistakenly removed these constraints in #227 under the assumption that
they were redundant, but they are actually required when building with
`transformers-0.6.*` due to `MonadTrans` having a quantified `Monad`
superclass.
Relax constraints for Free monad from applicative

Drop redundant constraints

Now that we support GHC 8.0 as the minimum, we are free to drop several
redundant constraints that were only around previously to support pre-AMP
GHCs.
Add nix shell with x11 libraries

Add Eq(1) and Ord(1) instances for the free applicative (#220)

* Add Eq/Eq1/Ord/Ord1 instances on free Applicative

* Fix for older environment (base <4.9, etc)

* Fix few mistakes

* Add explainations of the definitions of Eq1/Ord1

* Minor English-language prose tweaks

Co-authored-by: Ryan Scott <rscott@galois.com>

Simplify the Eq/Ord instances for FT

While slightly more verbose, the new instance contexts avoid the need for
overlapping instances or `FlexibleContexts`.

Allow building with transformers-0.6.* and mtl-2.3.*

Fixes #215.
